      "name": "Relative hemolysis index validation — experimental vs CFD prediction",
      "description": "Experimental hemolysis measurements using modified index of hemolysis (MIH) protocol with porcine blood at 37°C. Five flow-speed operating points tested in triplicate. CFD-predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) converted to relative hemolysis index (RH) and compared against experimental RH values. RH < 1 for all operating points confirms model identifies worst-case conditions correctly.",
      "comparisonMetric": "Relative hemolysis index RH",
      "comparisonValue": "0.87 (maximum across 5 operating points)",
      "acceptanceCriterion": "RH < 1.0 for all operating points",
      "passed": true,
      "hasUncertaintyQuantification": "https://uofa.net/synth/uq/morrison-uq-hemolysis-experimental-variability"
    },
    {
