    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/morrison-cou1-decision-001",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. Six factors are appropriately scoped as not-assessed at MRL 2. Validation results demonstrate CFD model predicts hemolysis index within acceptance criteria across all five operating points (RH < 1.0, maximum observed 0.87). Discretization error quantified via GCI (maximum 3.2%). Pressure rise and velocity field agreement confirmed. Aleatory uncertainty from biological variability and manufacturing tolerances is acknowledged in the validation narrative; formal UQ linkage is established for hemolysis experimental variability and discretization error. The assessment team accepts residual uncharacterized aleatory uncertainty in the flow field and wall shear stress results as consistent with MRL 2 requirements. Decision: Accepted for intended use.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z"
  },
